    "long_instructions": "## AI as Pilot. You as Co-Pilot.\r\n\r\nSwitch roles by prompting AI to make the same type of creative content that you did in the previous part.\r\n\r\nOn this level:\r\n- **AI Chat** will act as the **pilot**, drafting and making all the updates to the social media post.\r\n- **You** will act as a **co-pilot**, giving AI Chat suggestions to improve the social media post it writes.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Tell AI to write the same type of **social media post** you did earlier\r\n   - For example, *\"Write a post hyping up an upcoming volleyball game against our rivals the Coyotes.\"*\r\n2. **Record AI’s initial response** in your Activity Guide.\r\n3. Give AI **suggestions on how to improve** the post and **prompt AI to refine** the output.\r\n    - For example, _“The part about the bird leaving its cage doesn’t make sense. Revise it so that it does.” or “There aren't any emojis in your post . Revise it to include some.”_\r\n5. **Refine AI’s output** one more time by giving the AI at least one more suggestion\r\n6. Record AI’s final **refined output** in your Activity Guide.\r\n\r\n**Try it out!**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure what format to tell the AI to refine?**]\r\nGo back to Lesson 8: Debugging and Refining Outputs in your Unit Guide to review the information on the **Five Key Elements of a Prompt:**\r\n- **Task** - Specific and actionable instructions \r\n- **Context** - Relevant background details\r\n- **Format** - How the response should be structured\r\n- **Reference** - Additional examples or resources\r\n- **Tone** - The style in which the output is given\r\n:::",
